# --- 2nd release --------------------------------------------------------------
* marco Testframework, which will auto-test all ENCODING and METHOD's, before
	releasing.
* tinu  provide testfiles *.mp3 to marco for using in the testframework
* tinu  history/statistics
        in debug mode: write how much files were splitted with mp3splt
* marco -i -o options for custom input/output directories
* tinu  dontlike/ folder + manpage documentation

# --- later --------------------------------------------------------------------
* tinu  cross correlation with well known ad files
* tinu  maybe we could use ffmpeg instead of sox/lame 

